reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice small table
reviews.reviewText: This table is very small. It's shorter than a bedside table or couch table. It is better to use as an accent table. I have it near my sliding glass door with flameless candles on it and decorations. It brightens up the room but if you are looking for a taller table this one isn't it. It is very small.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A bit on the smaller side.
reviews.reviewText: It’s not a true side table or nightstand. It’s cute though. Sturdy wood, beautiful finish. It’s more of an accent table.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The measurements are accurate, so I can’t fault them for that. The sofa photo is totally deceptive. This table does not come close to being the height of a sofa seat. Otherwise it’s not bad, just comically small next to normal furniture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute Little Accent Table
reviews.reviewText: This is a cute little accent table. It is ideal for small spaces. I have a small condo and need little furniture both in the living room and bedroom. This table is perfect as either an end table or night table. It would also be useful just as a little extra side table. It's super easy to put together, you just need to screw in the legs. For the price, I think it's a great find.
